         <div type="entry">
                <head>Behnam Ḥadloyo</head>
                <ab type="idnos">
                    <idno type="URI">https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Behnam-Hadloyo</idno>
                    <idno type="syriaca-bibl">http://syriaca.org/bibl/101</idno>
                    <idno type="entry">92</idno>
                    <milestone unit="pages" n="68"/>
                    <idno type="subject">http://syriaca.org/person/263</idno>
                    <note type="type">person</note>
                    <note type="abstract">
                        <abbr>Patr.</abbr> and liturgical composer.<note/>
                    </note>
                </ab>
                <ab type="infobox">(d. 1454) [<abbr>Syr. Orth.</abbr>]</ab>
                <div type="body">
                    <p>
                        <abbr>Patr.</abbr> and liturgical composer. He was born in Ḥadl of Yūḥannā of the Habbo
                        Kanni family of <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Bartelle">
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/260">Barṭelle</placeName>
                        </ref>. He
                        became a monk at the <ref rend="bold"
                       target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Gabriel-Monastery-of-Mor">
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/226">Monastery of Mor Gabriel</placeName>
                        </ref>, was consecrated a Maph. and named
                        Baselius in 1404, and then a <abbr>
                            <choice>
                                <sic>Patr.</sic>
                                <corr>patr.</corr>
                            </choice>
                        </abbr> for the see of <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Mardin">
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/130">Mardin</placeName>
                        </ref> on June 1412.
                        After the death of the <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Tur-Abdin">
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/221">Ṭur ʿAbdin</placeName>
                        </ref>
                        anti-<abbr>patr.</abbr> Baselius V, he managed to unite all the dioceses under his
                        authority in 1445. He composed ten <hi rend="italic">ḥusoye</hi>, an
                        Anaphora, and 11 poems. He also compiled selections from the commentary of
                            <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Daniel-of-Salah">
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/59">Daniel of Salaḥ</persName>
                        </ref> and arranged them with the texts of the Psalms in
                        an autograph <abbr>ms.</abbr> dated 1425 (<abbr>ms.</abbr> Jerusalem, St. Mark 14).</p>
                </div>
